  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2037",
  "title": "[range slider] When min === max, the render is null",
  "body": "Bug.\r\n\r\nFrom what I've [read in the code](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/develop/src/components/Slider/Slider.js#L26-L30), when passing min, max with min===max, it breaks the underlying implementation, that's why we're displaying nothing.\r\n\r\nHowever, the widget implements a `autoHideContainer` with this exact predicate. This means that even if we set autoHideContainer to `false`, nothing will ever be displayed.\r\n\r\n## Ideas for a fix\r\n\r\n - Since it breaks the underlying implementation, we could display a message?\r\n - We could provide refine with slightly different values so that it doesn't break?\r\n\r\n## Reproducing the bug\r\n\r\nhttp://codepen.io/team/algolia/pen/42391e8ff756274bc148f915823177bc/\r\n\r\n - type `bless` in the query -> range slider is displayed\r\n - type `blessin` in the query -> no more range sliders even there is `autoHideContainer:false` in the config\r\n",
